# RAC Backend Implementation Plan

## Overview

Build out the backend for the RAC clone to support three core flows:
1. **Admin Login** — authenticate admin users
2. **Create Policy** — admin fills the form, policy is saved to DB, confirmation email is sent to the policyholder
3. **Retrieve Info** — user enters surname + DOB + postcode, and their policy details are displayed

---

## Tech Stack Decisions

| Layer | Choice | Why |
|---|---|---|
| **API** | Next.js API Routes (`/src/app/api/...`) | Already using Next.js — zero extra infra |
| **Database** | SQLite via **better-sqlite3** | File-based, no external DB server needed, perfect for this scale |
| **Email** | **Nodemailer** with Gmail SMTP | Free, simple, reliable |
| **Auth** | Simple session token stored in a cookie | Lightweight, no external auth provider needed |

> [!IMPORTANT]
> You will need a Gmail account with an **App Password** (not your regular password). We will configure this via a `.env.local` file that is never committed to git.

---

